            <thetext>As already suggested by Sebastian at Bug #1783 (Comment #2) we need to add a browser detection to get information about the browser *not* the engine.

For e.g. IE8 the engine detection indentifies IE8 in quirks mode as IE7 which leads to several problems when IE8 in quirks mode has another behaviour than the original IE7. If IE8 runs in this mode one cannot differ anymore.

As suggested a &quot;qx.bom.client.Browser&quot; class is the way to go.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
